dismissalText.commentary: Sharjeel Khan lbw b Malinga 7 (6b 1x4 0x6 11m) SR: 116.66

dismissalComment.html: cramps him for room with an angled delivery, but the bowler appeals and he gets the decision in his favour. Sharjeel has gone to review that. The appeal sounded a bit strange to the naked eye as it seemed he had hit it with the bat, but the replays show that it has flicked the front pad before the bat. The batsman was stuck in the crease. The ball hit the pad in line with stumps, but there is a question about height. It is hitting the top of middle and Pakistan have lost their review. Good tight decision by the umpire though. Sharjeel falls early after an impressive innings in the last game.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez run out (Karunaratne/†Sangakkara) 32 (52b 3x4 0x6 80m) SR: 61.53

dismissalComment.html: this time he nudges it past the midwicket fielder and calls for the second! But hello hello, where was the second in that? The fielder was charging from the deep and was on to it in a flash, fires in a good throw at the striker's end and Hafeez is nowhere in the frame. Someone predicted earlier it was going to be a run out and it is..A waste of a wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Kusal Perera run out (Bilawal Bhatti) 16 (24b 2x4 0x6 36m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: quicker delivery, he chops it to point and calls for a single, but it was straight to the fielder.. Dilshan, what have you done! KJP had no chance as it went straight to the fielder and all Bilawal hits the stumps direct.. Game over for KJP, for no fault of his. Pakistan have a bonus wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan run out (Mohammad Hafeez) 40 (48b 6x4 0x6 65m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: this time there is a direct hit from midwicket and Dilshan could be in trouble! He pulled it straight to midwicket and called for a quick one, but this is disaster for Dilshan as his bat just got stuck before the line and then came off his hands.. The ball strikes the stumps moments later, but Dilshan's bat is out of his hands and he is gone.. What luck! It got stuck into the pitch almost on the line.. One inch forward and Dilshan would have been fine.. Second direct hit from Pakistan, great work there by Hafeez, and second wicket.. this time it's a big one

commentPreTextItems.html: Two runs, three balls..Take it easy, says Lala to his troops

commentTextItems.html: but Sena does it! He has made sure Angelo's and Sanga's effort is not in vain. Cuts it fine between backward point and short third man for the winning runs

commentTextItems.html: a quick short ball that is hit only as far as midwicket. A throw is fired to the non-striker's end. Angelo dives to get in. A direct hit would have made the match interesting..

commentPreTextItems.html: Junaid comes to bowl the penultimate over.. 16 required.. That's more than what SA required a few days back off the last two overs against Pakistan

commentTextItems.html: fires a quick yorker, but it's a low full toss that is punched to wide long on for a couple
full delivery on the stumps, the batsman can only flick it to deep square leg, just a single

commentPostTextItems.html: Only five runs in that over.. Tanvir delivers

he flicks that with the angle to the leg side, but that is hit straight to short fine leg.. A meter here or a meter there, it was surely a boundary
bowls it tight on the stumps, the batsman wanted to pull it to the leg side, but gets a bottom edge on to his thigh pad. they run a single to square leg though
this time he punches it to extra cover for a single

commentPreTextItems.html: This is surely in the bag for SL now.. 21 off 18.. but you never know. Sohail Tanvir comes back.. won't be the choice if cricinfo feedbackers were asked..

commentTextItems.html: he bowls this one wide outside off! Angelo was making room and had to stretch to play that, he bunts it to off
now he tries to go for a sweep on one that is well outside off, misses it completely

commentPreTextItems.html: ashrit: "Sensible cricket from this both dis the advantage of having a genuine batsmen at 8"

commentTextItems.html: oh good ball, this one kept coming in to the left-hander and he inside edges it between his legs
they are not taking any risks off Ajmal. Angelo dabs it to the leg side and takes off for an easy one

commentPreTextItems.html: It's been an amazing nail-biter. Andrew Fernando is updating his match report as I type and there will be more news later. So keep an eye for it. Thanks for yours comments and feedback, it's time to say goodbye. Devashish Fuloria signing off. Ciao cioa.
<hr/>

"The amount of talent that we have got, it's unbelievable," Mathews says."The way Sanga and Chandimal batted, they set it up for us. Initially, Malinga and Kulasekara bowled really well to pull them back. They were cruising at 160 for 3 and were set for a biggie. Prasanna is an unbelivable player, he can hit the ball a long way, but I had to share my thoughts, my experience with him. I am glad we were able to pull it through. It was a good fighting performance today."

"Looking at the wicket, it was really a good score,"Misbah says."We were in control, but one or two bad overs cost us the game. You have to be there for the full 100 overs. They are a good team and we know each other very well, so it's game on."

Ahmed Shehzad is the Golden Player of the Match, Shahid Afridi wins the Master Blaster award and Junaid Khan wins some cash too for his bowling. He is the Circle Player of the Match. Ahmed Shehzad gets a Highest scorer award.. The list is unending. Junaid is back to collect another prize for outstanding performance.. Wait. There is another one. Ahmed Shehzad gets one for hitting most fours... And of course, there is the final award. Angelo gets something. He is the Man of the Match
<hr/>

What a cracker! Sri Lanka are back in the series with a plucky win here. The series goes 1-1. Pakistan bowlers pulled things back magnificently after Dilshan and KJP had given Sri Lanka a good start, but Sanga and Chandimal didn't give it away in the face of some good bowling..Then they started playing their shots. Then they got out.. But Angelo and a little cameo from Kula as well, they all added up..A nailbiting two-wicket win for Sri Lanka. Well played both teams.
Gayan: "The Mathews & Karunaratne partnership is something that's theoretically very easy, but given the situation - very tough to achieve. Nice work by both teams. Loving this series."
Vinoj Jayasundara: "SL clearly enjoying the benefit of having 10 batsmen in the team..."
Andy: "The best thing that Sri Lanka takes out of this game is not the win but the knowledge that Dimuth Karunaratne is a much better choice for the ODI team than Lahiru Thirimanne."
Chathuranga: "Yeeeeeeeeeeee we won the match... Congratulations Sri Lanka......!!!! I wish if I could be in Dubai to celebrate the victory...!!!"
RK: "Very impressed by Mathews' calm attitude. May not be the best captain, but he's getting there."

AliJee: "Things would have been different if Mishab has brought his strike bowlers early in the innings. He made SL to build up their innings & confidence, applying his best when Sanga & Chandima were well set. It was fairly a difficult looking total. But cracking knock by the captain & well played SL."
Essam: "Those four overthrows are now looking more than painful."

Sharjeel falls early after an impressive innings in the last game.

dismissalComment.html: oh that is the end of Shehzad! He was trying to flick the yorker fine by shuffling across the stumps and he missed it.. It hit the front pad and would have crashed on to off and middle. A good innings by Shehzad comes to an end..

dismissalText.commentary: Kusal Perera run out (Bilawal Bhatti) 16 (24b 2x4 0x6 36m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: quicker delivery, he chops it to point and calls for a single, but it was straight to the fielder.. Dilshan, what have you done! KJP had no chance as it went straight to the fielder and all Bilawal hits the stumps direct.. Game over for KJP, for no fault of his. Pakistan have a bonus wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan run out (Mohammad Hafeez) 40 (48b 6x4 0x6 65m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: this time there is a direct hit from midwicket and Dilshan could be in trouble! He pulled it straight to midwicket and called for a quick one, but this is disaster for Dilshan as his bat just got stuck before the line and then came off his hands.. The ball strikes the stumps moments later, but Dilshan's bat is out of his hands and he is gone.. What luck! It got stuck into the pitch almost on the line.. One inch forward and Dilshan would have been fine.. Second direct hit from Pakistan, great work there by Hafeez, and second wicket.. this time it's a big one

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara b Saeed Ajmal 58 (67b 4x4 1x6 109m) SR: 86.56

dismissalComment.html: oh that's the big wicket! Clatter of the stumps as Sanga gets a bottom edge on to the stumps. It was quicker delivery and he wanted to slog sweep it, but missed it. Ajmal is ecstatic, so is Pakistan..

dismissalComment.html: now Junaid strikes to remove the other set batsman! This one was quick from round the wicket, angling in and Chandimal, who was neither forward nor back, was a little late to bring his bat down. He looses his off stump and Pakistan take further control
